 <H1>Multi-Attribute Index Keys</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>To retrieve Emp records with age=30 AND sal=4000, an index on <age,sal> would be better than an index on age or an index on sal.
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Such indexes also called composite or concatenated indexes.
<LI>Choice of index key orthogonal to clustering etc.
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>If condition is:  20<age<30  AND  3000<sal<5000: 
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Clustered tree index on <age,sal> or <sal,age> is best.
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>If condition is:  age=30  AND  3000<sal<5000: 
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Clustered <age,sal> index much better than <sal,age> index!
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Composite indexes are larger, updated more often.</H2></P>

<P></UL></P>

